A hospital in Canada is treating a patient with flu-like symptoms similar to what an outbreak of the deadly Ebola virus would look like.

The patient is being held in isolation at the Brampton Civic Hospital in Ontario after returning from a trip to Nigeria, which on Friday declared a state of emergency because of the disease.

'Initial signs and symptoms of Ebola are 
similar to many more common diseases,' cautioned Ontario's health minister, Eric Hoskins.

'One such disease relevant to 
African travel is malaria. There are currently no confirmed cases of 
Ebola in Ontario.'

