'Countries affected to date simply do not have the capacity to manage an outbreak of this size and complexity on their own,' Chan told reporters in Geneva.

'I urge the international community to provide this support on the most urgent basis possible.'

In the United States, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention have already elevated their Ebola response to the highest level and have recommended against traveling to West Africa.

On Thursday, CDC director Dr. Tom Frieden told a Congressional hearing that the current outbreak is set to sicken more people than all previous outbreaks of the disease combined.

